With Krishnakumar. Adat, Kole Wetlands, Thrissur
male (?) calling from ground concealed in thick scrub.  call was unknown to me.  ID from XC266600.  3 birds of same species were seen about 20 metres away

Please note the the Identification is a correction. Originally given as "Red-legged Crake" and mentioned as such in:

Trainor, C. R., Verbelen, P, and Johnstone, R. E. (2012). The avifauna of Alor and Pantar, Lesser Sundas, Indonesia. Forktail – Journal of Asian Ornithology 28: 77-92.

The correction was brought to my attention by Filip Verbelen and John Hornbuckle, because John Hornbuckle [I think used my recordings on Alor], but only attracted Ruddy-breasted Crake.

Other recordings on Xeno-Canto that sound the same, and belong to Ruddy-breasted.

Birds were not observed by me.
